name: 2-Ethyloxirane
Reason: 2-Ethyloxirane has a melting point of -100.0 degrees Celsius. The basic unit, ethane, has a melting point of -172.0 degrees Celsius. Fluorine substituents significantly increase the melting point due to strong electronegativity which leads to stronger intermolecular dipole-dipole interactions. Each fluorine is estimated to increase the melting point by approximately 15 degrees Celsius, giving a total increase of (15 degrees Celsius x 2 fluorines) = 30 degrees Celsius.
